    {
      "id": "PopularPost208941",
      "post_content": "Why do people keep saying \"[ponder](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=ponder)\" and such. This is an instant. If you know how to play blue at it's best, as it was meant to be played as it were, then you NEED instant speed. Instant speed means you leave your mana open for a counterspell of some kind, if they don't play something you want to counter, you just start card drawing. The only reason stuff like this can't make it in vintage is:  \n-[Brainstorm](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Brainstorm)  \n-\"Free\" counterspells (meaning no reason to leave mana open if you'd rather draw now => higher drawing power)  \n  \nInstant speed makes or breaks draw cards. New kids on the block at sorcery speed are what it takes to make a sorcery speed one even compete. Note also that it does clear the way of up to two cards. Even if neither is what you needed this fixes the next two problems you may have had.   \n  \nA year ago I got this and didn't know what I was doing so I stopped using it. Now I use it because it blows [Ponder](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Ponder) and such out of t... [(see all)](javascript:void(0);)",
      "posted_by": "blurrymadness",
      "html": "<div class=\"post oddItem\" id=\"PopularPost208941\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl07_post\">Why do people keep saying \"<a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"ponder\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=ponder\">ponder</a>\" and such. This is an instant. If you know how to play blue at it's best, as it was meant to be played as it were, then you NEED instant speed. Instant speed means you leave your mana open for a counterspell of some kind, if they don't play something you want to counter, you just start card drawing. The only reason stuff like this can't make it in vintage is:<br/>-<a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Brainstorm\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Brainstorm\">Brainstorm</a><br/>-\"Free\" counterspells (meaning no reason to leave mana open if you'd rather draw now =&gt; higher drawing power)<br/><br/>Instant speed makes or breaks draw cards. New kids on the block at sorcery speed are what it takes to make a sorcery speed one even compete. Note also that it does clear the way of up to two cards. Even if neither is what you needed this fixes the next two problems you may have had. <br/><br/>A year ago I got this and didn't know what I was doing so I stopped using it. Now I use it because it blows <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Ponder\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Ponder\">Ponder</a> and such out of t... <a href=\"javascript:void(0);\" onclick=\"ExpandPost(event, this, 208941)\">(see all)</a></span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl07_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"http://wizards.custhelp.com/cgi-bin/wizards.cfg/php/enduser/ask.php?p_prods=522,706,739&amp;p_cats=\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl07_reportAbuseLink\" onclick=\"HandleReportPost